 {id:"c2g_nominalisation",title:"Nominalizace",type:"grammar",theory:"V akademickém a formálním psaní se slovesa často mění na abstraktní podstatná jména (nominalizace), což zní formálněji: analyze → <b>analysis</b>, decide → <b>decision</b>, argue → <b>argument</b>.",table:[["Sloveso","Nominalizace"],["decide","decision"],["analyse","analysis"],["argue","argument"],["implement","implementation"]],items:[["The committee reached a final ___ .","decision",["decision","decide","deciding"],"Výbor dospěl ke konečnému rozhodnutí."],["Further ___ of the data is required.","analysis",["analysis","analyse","analysing"],"Je potřeba další analýza dat."],["His ___ was based on weak evidence.","argument",["argument","argue","arguing"],"Jeho argument byl založen na slabých důkazech."],["The ___ of the new law caused controversy.","implementation",["implementation","implement","implementing"],"Zavedení nového zákona vyvolalo kontroverzi."],["There was strong ___ to the proposal.","opposition",["opposition","oppose","opposing"],"Proti návrhu byl silný odpor."],["The ___ of resources was unfair.","distribution",["distribution","distribute","distributing"],"Rozdělení zdrojů bylo nespravedlivé."],["Their ___ of the contract took months.","negotiation",["negotiation","negotiate","negotiating"],"Vyjednávání smlouvy trvalo měsíce."],["The ___ of the building took two years.","construction",["construction","construct","constructing"],"Výstavba budovy trvala dva roky."],["Public ___ to the plan grew quickly.","reaction",["reaction","react","reacting"],"Veřejná reakce na plán rychle rostla."],["The company announced the ___ of the merger.","completion",["completion","complete","completing"],"Firma oznámila dokončení fúze."]]},
 {id:"c2g_hedging",title:"Hedging (zmírňování tvrzení)",type:"grammar",theory:"V akademickém a formálním jazyce se tvrzení často zmírňují (hedging), aby nezněla příliš kategoricky: <b>It could be argued that…</b>, <b>This may suggest…</b>, <b>It seems likely that…</b>",table:[["Výraz","Příklad"],["It could be argued that","It could be argued that..."],["It seems likely that","It seems likely that..."],["This may suggest","This may suggest..."]],items:[["It ___ be argued that the policy failed.","could",["could","is","was"],"Dalo by se argumentovat, že politika selhala."],["This may ___ a wider problem.","suggest",["suggest","suggests","suggested"],"To může naznačovat širší problém."],["It seems ___ that prices will rise.","likely",["likely","like","likelihood"],"Zdá se pravděpodobné, že ceny porostou."],["The results ___ to indicate a correlation.","appear",["appear","appears","appeared"],"Výsledky se zdají naznačovat souvislost."],["It is ___ possible that further research is needed.","arguably",["arguably","argue","argued"],"Je zřejmě možné, že je potřeba další výzkum."],["One might ___ that the data is incomplete.","argue",["argue","arguing","argued"],"Dalo by se namítnout, že data jsou neúplná."],["This finding ___ to support the theory.","tends",["tend","tends","tended"],"Toto zjištění má sklon podporovat teorii."],["It would ___ that more evidence is required.","seem",["seem","seems","seemed"],"Zdálo by se, že je zapotřebí více důkazů."],["The claim is ___ open to interpretation.","somewhat",["somewhat","some","such"],"Tvrzení je poněkud otevřené interpretaci."],["It is not ___ that the results are conclusive.","entirely",["entirely","entire","entity"],"Není zcela jisté, že výsledky jsou průkazné."]]},
 {id:"c2g_ellipsis",title:"Elipsa (so / neither)",type:"grammar",theory:"V pokročilé angličtině se opakující se sloveso často nahrazuje pomocí <b>so</b> (souhlas v kladu) nebo <b>neither/nor</b> (souhlas v záporu), aby se předešlo opakování: He passed, and so <b>did</b> she. I don't like it, and neither <b>does</b> he.",table:[["Vzorec","Příklad"],["…, and so + pomocné sloveso + podmět","...and so did she."],["…, and neither + pomocné sloveso + podmět","...and neither does he."]],items:[["He passed the exam, and so ___ she.","did",["did","does","do"],"On zkoušku udělal, a ona také."],["I don't like coffee, and neither ___ my brother.","does",["does","do","did"],"Nemám rád kávu, a můj bratr taky ne."],["She can swim, and so ___ I.","can",["can","do","does"],"Ona umí plavat, a já taky."],["He hasn't finished, and neither ___ I.","have",["have","has","do"],"On nedokončil, a já taky ne."],["They will come, and so ___ we.","will",["will","do","are"],"Oni přijdou, a my taky."],["I'm tired, and so ___ she.","is",["is","are","am"],"Jsem unavený, a ona taky."],["He didn't call, and neither ___ she.","did",["did","does","do"],"On nezavolal, a ona taky ne."],["We were late, and so ___ they.","were",["were","was","are"],"Přišli jsme pozdě, a oni taky."],["She'd already left, and so ___ he.","had",["had","has","did"],"Ona už odešla, a on taky."],["I wouldn't do that, and neither ___ you.","would",["would","will","should"],"Já bych to neudělal, a ty taky ne."]]},
 {id:"c2g_collocation",title:"Pokročilé kolokace",type:"grammar",theory:"Přirozená plynulost vyžaduje znalost kolokací — slovních spojení, která rodilí mluvčí používají spolu: <b>make a decision</b> (ne 'do a decision'), <b>heavy rain</b> (ne 'strong rain').",table:[["Sloveso","Typická kolokace"],["make","a decision, an effort, a profit"],["take","a risk, advantage, a record"],["do","your best"]],items:[["She finally ___ a decision after much thought.","made",["made","did","took"],"Nakonec se po dlouhém přemýšlení rozhodla."],["It was raining ___ all weekend.","heavily",["heavily","strongly","hardly"],"Celý víkend hustě pršelo."],["He ___ a great effort to finish on time.","made",["made","did","took"],"Vynaložil velké úsilí, aby to stihl včas."],["They ___ a huge risk by investing everything.","took",["took","made","did"],"Podstoupili obrovské riziko tím, že investovali všechno."],["The company ___ a profit last quarter.","made",["made","did","took"],"Firma minulé čtvrtletí vytvořila zisk."],["She pays close ___ to detail.","attention",["attention","care","notice"],"Věnuje velkou pozornost detailům."],["He ___ his best but still failed.","did",["did","made","took"],"Udělal, co mohl, ale přesto neuspěl."],["It's important to ___ advantage of every opportunity.","take",["take","make","do"],"Je důležité využít každé příležitosti."],["They reached a mutual ___ after negotiations.","agreement",["agreement","decision","deal"],"Po jednáních dosáhli vzájemné dohody."],["He set a new world ___ in the race.","record",["record","rank","mark"],"V závodě vytvořil nový světový rekord."]]},
 {id:"c2g_advinversion",title:"Inverze místo if",type:"grammar",theory:"V C2 formálním stylu lze <b>if</b> vynechat a použít inverzi: <b>Had I known</b>, I would have called. <b>Were she here</b>, she would help. <b>Should you need</b> anything, let me know.",table:[["Vzorec","Náhrada za","Příklad"],["Had + podmět + 3. tvar","If + had","Had I known..."],["Were + podmět","If + was/were","Were she here..."],["Should + podmět","If + should","Should you need..."]],items:[["___ I known, I would have acted differently.","Had",["Had","Have","Would"],"Kdybych to byl věděl, jednal bych jinak."],["___ she here, she would know what to do.","Were",["Were","Was","Is"],"Kdyby tu byla, věděla by, co dělat."],["___ you need any help, just call me.","Should",["Should","Would","Could"],"Kdybys potřeboval pomoc, prostě zavolej."],["___ we not intervened, the situation would have worsened.","Had",["Had","Have","Were"],"Kdybychom nezasáhli, situace by se zhoršila."],["___ it not for your help, I would have failed.","Were",["Were","Was","Had"],"Nebýt tvé pomoci, neuspěl bych."],["___ he arrive late, please let him in.","Should",["Should","Would","Could"],"Kdyby přišel pozdě, prosím pusťte ho dovnitř."],["___ I to win the lottery, I'd travel the world.","Were",["Were","Was","Had"],"Kdybych náhodou vyhrál v loterii, procestoval bych svět."],["___ they known the risks, they wouldn't have agreed.","Had",["Had","Have","Were"],"Kdyby byli znali rizika, nesouhlasili by."],["___ any issues arise, contact us immediately.","Should",["Should","Would","Could"],"Kdyby nastaly nějaké problémy, kontaktujte nás okamžitě."],["___ she not been there, the accident would have been worse.","Had",["Had","Have","Were"],"Kdyby tam nebyla, nehoda by byla horší."]]}
